   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The first step is to apply the specified voltages to the terminals
for the system.</p>
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that <xref href="1220236_Preparations_with_Power_Off_CPT_DD00561515.dita"
                        scope="local"
                        type="concept"
                        class="- topic/xref "/> have been performed.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Technical Data</i> and <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Connection
Diagram</i> for the specifications of the DC input power voltage and
polarity.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Connect the DC input power voltage to the open
inverter input switch. Keep the switch open!</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Measure and check with a properly rated measuring
device that the DC input power voltage (L+, L- and ground) and polarity
are according to specifications.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Technical Data</i> and <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Connection Diagram</i> for
the specifications of the bypass mains voltage, frequency and phase
sequence.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Connect the bypass mains voltage to the open EN (BYP SSW) input
switch. Keep the switch open!</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Measure and check with a properly rated measuring device that
the bypass mains voltage, frequency and phase sequence are according
to specifications.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
